artifacts.summary: Comprehensive enumeration of all temporal connection constraints between consecutive MCSs; confirms user's 4 constraints hold; identifies FIX tag (reflexive operators); proves no additional constraints resolve forward_F/backward_P obstruction; analyzes F-preserving seed conjecture proof obstacle (G-lifting fails)

partial_progress.details: Research report written (393 lines). Enumerated 10 constraints (6 proven, 2 derivable, 1 construction-based, 1 confirmed non-constraint). Verified all 4 user-listed constraints. Confirmed FIX tag: operators are reflexive not strict. Analyzed IDEA tag: G/neg(G) reframing valid but same obstacle. F-preserving seed conjecture remains open at 55% confidence.
partial_progress.key_finding: All four user-listed temporal connection constraints are verified. The constraint enumeration is exhaustive for TM logic. No additional constraints resolve the forward_F/backward_P obstruction. The F-preserving seed conjecture's proof obstacle is specifically that G-lifting cannot handle neg(G(theta)) formulas in the seed -- a semantic argument (model construction) may succeed where the syntactic approach fails.
